<section>
<title>Let's Summarize</title>
<body>
<p>In general, a confidence interval for
                    <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101126T110200-0500"?>the
                    <?oxy_insert_end?>unknown population proportion
                    <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101126T110221-0500"?>(<?oxy_insert_end?>p<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101126T110222-0500"?>)<?oxy_insert_end?>
                    is <m:math overflow="scroll">
                        <m:mrow>
                            <m:mover>
                                <m:mi>p</m:mi>
                                <m:mo stretchy="true">ˆ</m:mo>
                            </m:mover>
                            <m:mo>±</m:mo>
                            <m:msup>
                                <m:mi>z</m:mi>
                                <m:mo>*</m:mo>
                            </m:msup>
                            <m:mo>⋅</m:mo>
                            <m:msqrt>
                                <m:mfrac>
                                    <m:mrow>
                                        <m:mover>
                                            <m:mi>p</m:mi>
                                            <m:mo stretchy="true">ˆ</m:mo>
                                        </m:mover>
                                        <m:mfenced open="(" close=")">
                                            <m:mrow>
                                                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                                                <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                                                <m:mover>
                                                  <m:mi>p</m:mi>
                                                  <m:mo stretchy="true">ˆ</m:mo>
                                                </m:mover>
                                            </m:mrow>
                                        </m:mfenced>
                                    </m:mrow>
                                    <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                                </m:mfrac>
                            </m:msqrt>
                        </m:mrow>
                    </m:math>, where z* is 1.645 for 90% confidence, 2 for 95% confidence, and 2.576
                    for 99% confidence.</p>
<p>To obtain a desired margin of error
                    <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101126T110210-0500"?>(<?oxy_insert_end?>m<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101126T110212-0500"?>)<?oxy_insert_end?>
                    in a confidence interval
                    for<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101126T110248-0500"?>
                    an<?oxy_insert_end?> unknown population proportion, a conservative sample
                    size<?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101126T110541-0500" content=" to take"?>
                    is <m:math overflow="scroll">
                        <m:mrow>
                            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                            <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                            <m:mfrac>
                                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                                <m:msup>
                                    <m:mi>m</m:mi>
                                    <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                                </m:msup>
                            </m:mfrac>
                        </m:mrow>
                    </m:math>.</p>
<p>The margin of error of a poll is determined (conservatively) by <m:math overflow="scroll">
<m:mrow>
<m:mfrac>
<m:mn>1</m:mn>
<m:msqrt>
<m:mi>n</m:mi>
</m:msqrt>
</m:mfrac>
</m:mrow>
</m:math>.</p>
<p>The methods developed in this unit are safe to use as long as
                        <?oxy_comment_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101126T110633-0500" comment="Suggest using asterisks rather than dots for multiplication"?><m:math
                        overflow="scroll">
                        <m:mrow>
                            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                            <m:mo>⋅</m:mo>
                            <m:mover>
                                <m:mi>p</m:mi>
                                <m:mo stretchy="true">ˆ</m:mo>
                            </m:mover>
                            <m:mo>≥</m:mo>
                            <m:mn>10</m:mn>
                        </m:mrow>
                    </m:math> and <m:math overflow="scroll">
                        <m:mrow>
                            <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                            <m:mo>⋅</m:mo>
                            <m:mfenced open="(" close=")">
                                <m:mrow>
                                    <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                                    <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                                    <m:mover>
                                        <m:mi>p</m:mi>
                                        <m:mo stretchy="true">ˆ</m:mo>
                                    </m:mover>
                                </m:mrow>
                            </m:mfenced>
                            <m:mo>≥</m:mo>
                            <m:mn>10</m:mn>
                        </m:mrow>
                    </m:math> .<?oxy_comment_end?></p>
<activity idref="_u5_m1_lbd6" purpose="learnbydoing"/>
<p> </p>
